name: 10,000,000 Volt Thunderbolt
efect: Pikachu-exclusive Z-Move. High critical hit ratio.

name: Anchor Shot
efect: The user entangles the target with its anchor chain while attacking. The target becomes unable to flee.

name: Aurora Veil
efect: Halves damage from Physical and Special attacks for five turns.

name: Baneful Bunker
efect: Protects the user and poisons opponent on contact.

name: Beak Blast
efect: The user first heats up its beak, and then it attacks the target. Making direct contact with the Pokémon while it's heating up its beak results in a burn.

name: Bouncy Bubble
efect: User recovers half the HP inflicted on opponent.

name: Brutal Swing
efect: The user swings its body around violently to inflict damage on everything in its vicinity.

name: Burn Up
efect: To inflict massive damage, the user burns itself out. After using this move, the user will no longer be Fire type.

name: Core Enforcer
efect: Suppresses the target's ability if the target has already moved.

name: Double Iron Bash
efect: Hits twice in one turn; may cause flinching.

name: Dragon Hammer
efect: The user uses its body like a hammer to attack the target and inflict damage.

name: Extreme Evoboost
efect: Eevee-exclusive Z-Move. Sharply raises all stats.

name: Fire Lash
efect: The user strikes the target with a burning lash. This also lowers the target's Defense stat.

name: First Impression
efect: Although this move has great power, it only works the first turn the user is in battle.

name: Floral Healing
efect: The user restores the target's HP by up to half of its max HP. It restores more HP when the terrain is grass.

name: Gear Up
efect: The user engages its gears to raise the Attack and Sp. Atk stats of ally Pokémon with the Plus or Minus Ability.

name: Guardian of Alola
efect: Tapu-exclusive Z-move. Cuts opponent's HP by 75%.

name: High Horsepower
efect: The user fiercely attacks the target using its entire body.

name: Ice Hammer
efect: The user swings and hits with its strong, heavy fist. It lowers the user's Speed, however.

name: Instruct
efect: Allows an ally to use a move instead.

name: Laser Focus
efect: User's next attack is guaranteed to result in a critical hit.

name: Light That Burns the Sky
efect: Ultra Necrozma-exclusive Z-Move. Ignores target's ability; uses highest Attack stat.

name: Lunge
efect: The user makes a lunge at the target, attacking with full force. This also lowers the target's Attack stat.

name: Photon Geyser
efect: Uses Attack or Special Attack stat, whichever is higher.

name: Pika Papow
efect: Power increases when player's bond is stronger.

name: Plasma Fists
efect: Changes Normal-type moves to Electric-type moves.

name: Pollen Puff
efect: Deals damage to opponent or restores HP of teammate.

name: Power Trip
efect: The user boasts its strength and attacks the target. The more the user's stats are raised, the greater the move's power.

name: Prismatic Laser
efect: The user shoots powerful lasers using the power of a prism. The user can't move on the next turn.

name: Psychic Fangs
efect: The user bites the target with its psychic capabilities. This can also destroy Light Screen and Reflect.

name: Psychic Terrain
efect: Prevents priority moves from being used for 5 turns.

name: Purify
efect: The user heals the target's status condition. If the move succeeds, it also restores the user's own HP.

name: Revelation Dance
efect: Type changes based on Oricorio's form.

name: Sappy Seed
efect: Drains HP from opponent each turn.

name: Shell Trap
efect: Deals more damage to opponent if hit by a Physical move.

name: Shore Up
efect: The user regains up to half of its max HP. It restores more HP in a sandstorm.

name: Smart Strike
efect: The user stabs the target with a sharp horn. This attack never misses.

name: Solar Blade
efect: Charges on first turn, attacks on second.

name: Sparkling Aria
efect: Heals the burns of its target.

name: Sparkly Swirl
efect: Cures all status problems in the party Pokémon.

name: Spectral Thief
efect: The user hides in the target's shadow, steals the target's stat boosts, and then attacks.

name: Speed Swap
efect: The user exchanges Speed stats with the target.

name: Spirit Shackle
efect: Prevents the opponent from switching out.

name: Spotlight
efect: The user shines a spotlight on the target so that only the target will be attacked during the turn.

name: Stomping Tantrum
efect: Driven by frustration, the user attacks the target. If the user's previous move has failed, the power of this move doubles.

name: Strength Sap
efect: The user restores its HP by the same amount as the target's Attack stat. It also lowers the target's Attack stat.

name: Tearful Look
efect: The user gets teary eyed to make the target lose its combative spirit. This lowers the target's Attack and Sp. Atk stats.

name: Throat Chop
efect: Prevents use of sound moves for two turns.

name: Toxic Thread
efect: Poisons opponent and lowers its Speed.

name: Veevee Volley
efect: Power increases when player's bond is stronger.

name: Zippy Zap
efect: Always results in a critical hit.
